<item>
<title><![CDATA[Just a fun little chicken stir fry 🕺🏻recipe below! Ingredients: ...]]></title>
<link>https://imginn.com/p/C_dYuDzOjoR/</link>
<guid>https://imginn.com/p/C_dYuDzOjoR/</guid>
<description>
<![CDATA[<a href="https://instagram.com/p/C_dYuDzOjoR/">View on Instagram</a><p><img src="https://scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.29350-15/458154685_1223455022184930_7822540487901024356_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15&_nc_ht=scontent-bos5-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=106&_nc_ohc=aJvzzUMHVL0Q7kNvgHHBvZX&_nc_gid=5aff82a0136849aa990abfa6622c3291&edm=AGenrX8BAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_AYBNOgdjkxmAeAE_qBukKALHs6kWi52gqP8x5Llb4oXO_g&oe=6710530C&_nc_sid=ed990e" /><br>Just a fun little chicken stir fry 🕺🏻recipe below! Ingredients: -1 chicken breast -1 servicing of rice noodles -small bunch of broccolini -3 green onions -3-4 garlic cloves (sliced) -2 eggs -soy sauce -limes-olive oil, salt and pepper Recipe: -prep everything: slice garlic, cut broccolini &amp; green onions in half, cut chicken breast into thin slices (butterfly and slice!), whisk together 2 eggs, cook rice noodles according to package (usually add boiling water for 2-5 min depending on the type you get)-heat a large pan (or wok) on medium heat. Add oil and chicken, season with salt and pepper. Cook for about 2 min. add garlic, broccolini, and green onions cook for another 2 min. Add a couple tbsp of soy sauce. Mix and remove from the pan. -wipe pan, add oil and eggs. Quickly scramble and add noodles, toss and add chicken and veggies back. Toss to coat and serve!! I like adding more green onions and some lime to the top 🫶🏼 recipe from @gordongram (he has a YT video if that’s helpful but it seriously takes under 10 min and is so good!) *for those curious: the fisheye clips are filmed on @gopro !! I used the max lens mod, turned off max lens mode, and turned off hyper smooth (otherwise the circle will move around) mounted it with a magnetic clip above my stove 😌*other shots filmed on my iPhone13 switching between cinematic and normal video!]]>
</description>
<pubDate>Thu, 12 Sep 2024 10:50:33 -0400</pubDate>
</item>
